Enum StruCheckCode

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<StruCheckCode>
      • org.rdkit.knime.nodes.structurenormalizer.StruCheckCode

    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<StruCheckCode>

    public enum StruCheckCode
extends java.lang.Enum<StruCheckCode>
    Defines Structure Checker Codes as used in the RDKit. This definition must match the definition used in RDKit.
    Author:
    Manuel Schwarze

      • getErrorCodeMask

        public static int getErrorCodeMask(StruCheckCode... arrAdditionalFailureCodes)
        Determines the bit mask for all codes that shall be treated as errors. Included will be all codes that are defined in ERROR_CODE_MASK and all codes that are passed in as parameter.
        Parameters:
        arrAdditionalFailureCodes - Additional codes that shall be treated as error.
        Returns:
        Bit mask of all error codes.

      • getNonErrorCodeMask

        public static int getNonErrorCodeMask(StruCheckCode... arrAdditionalFailureCodes)
        Determines the bit mask for all codes that shall not be treated as errors. Included will be all codes that are neither defined in ERROR_CODE_MASK nor passed in as parameter.
        Parameters:
        arrAdditionalFailureCodes - Additional codes that shall be treated as error.
        Returns:
        Bit mask of all non error codes.

      • getCodes

        public static StruCheckCode[] getCodes(int iFlags,
                                       int iBitMask)
        Returns an array of codes based on the passed in flags and the passed in bit mask. Only codes are returned that are set in both values.
        Parameters:
        iFlags - Flags with codes.
        iBitMask - Bit mask with codes that act as a filter.
        Returns:
        Array of codes, which can be empty, but never null.
